{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Sterol regulatory element-binding protein cleavage-activating protein (SCAP) is a escort protein required for cholesterol and lipid homeostasis [[cite:PUB00071989]]. It is an endoplasmic reticulum protein with eight transmembrane helices that serves as a cholesterol sensor [[cite:PUB00071991]]. In cholesterol-depleted cells, SCAP transports sterol regulatory element-binding proteins (SREBPs) to the Golgi, where the active fragment of SREBP is liberated by proteases so that it can activate genes for cholesterol synthesis [[cite:PUB00071990]].</p>\n\n<p>A homologue of SCAP exists in Schizosaccharomyces pombe, named Scp1, which together with Sre1 (homologue to SREBP), may mediate a hypoxic response by monitoring oxygen-dependent sterol synthesis [[cite:PUB00044954]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR46378" "STEROL REGULATORY ELEMENT-BINDING PROTEIN CLEAVAGE-ACTIVATING PROTEIN"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Sterol regulatory element-binding protein cleavage-activating protein", "short" "SCAP"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 8, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1711, "taxa" 5929, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3456, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3456, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1658}, "pathways" 3}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR030225", :literature {"PUB00071989" {"URL" nil, "issue" "10", "authors" ["Matsuda M" "Korn BS" "Hammer RE" "Moon YA" "Komuro R" "Horton JD" "Goldstein JL" "Brown MS" "Shimomura I."], "ISO_journal" "Genes Dev.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1101/gad.891301", "medline_journal" "Genes Dev", "title" "SREBP cleavage-activating protein (SCAP) is required for increased lipid synthesis in liver induced by cholesterol deprivation and insulin elevation.", "year" 2001, 